            <thetext>(In reply to comment #2)
&gt; Thomas, do you think we would need such a feature? I can very well live with 
an explicit target to supply. In what situation could a user really benefit 
from a default target?

It was not my requirement (although I filed the bug).

It might be interesting in a project that deviates from the standard 
&quot;source&quot;/&quot;build&quot; jobs for the top-level job names (like it is the case in big 
projects). A default job would support an unknowing user in &quot;getting the thing 
going&quot;, actually in both a standard or deviating project.

I&#39;m fine with explicit targets as well :).</thetext>
